observations.recommendation:
1.6     We have recommended and management agreed to:
a)  strictly adhere to laws, rules and regulations in the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances as provided in COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;
b)   expedite the disbursement of social pension funds to the senior citizens;
c)  through the Municipal Accountant, regularly monitor the liquidation of cash advances of officers and employees, and to deduct outstanding cash advances from salaries and other monetary claims of such officers and employees; and
d)   discontinue partial liquidation of cash advances.

a.  strengthen the monitoring and inspection mechanisms of the LGU, and proceed with the issuance of the Certificate of Completion after thorough evaluation of the projects as required;
b.  issue the Certificate of Final Acceptance after one (1) year from date of CoC to cover the Defects Liability Period; and
c.  impose on contractors WS with validity periods covering one year from CFA date.

a.  limit payroll deductions and follow the order of preference provided in the GAA to ensure that all employees’ take home pay shall not be less than the minimum allowed by law;
b.  cease from being a withholding agent for loan obligations of employees in institutions not allowed in the provisions above; and
c.  hold the withholding agents/officials responsible for allowing the net take home pay of the employees lesser than that allowed by law.

8.10   	We have recommended and management agreed to:
a. 	through the Municipal Accountant, implement strictly the guidelines provided under LBC No. 103 dated May 15, 2013, on the grant of Representation and Transportation Allowances to all LGU officials entitled thereto;
b.   cause the refund of overpaid RATA as identified herein;
c.   through the Vice-Mayor, as the presiding chair of the SB, instigate the adoption/inclusion of rules in the IRP on the work schedules/performance standards of all members, which shall be used in the determination of percentage of RATA to be granted hereafter, in accordance with Item 7.5 of the above LBC; and
d.  observe the rules on leave of absence.

through the GAD Focal Point, henceforth, administer the HGDG test on the LGU’s GAD PPAs in the preparation of Accomplishment Report, as basis for determining the actual expenditure that can be attributed to the GAD Budget;
administer the HGDG test on its PPAs for CY 2017, the results of which shall be the basis in estimating the cost of gender mainstreaming and GAD Budget;
if and when necessary, conduct a training program on the HGDG for the incoming year and seek assistance of a gender analysis expert in the use of and/administration of the HGDG; and
expedite the implementation of GAD PPAs to accelerate gender mainstreaming in the LGU operations.

14.5	We have recommended and management agreed to:
follow-up the approval of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan from the NSWMC, and thereafter, request for funding of relevant projects from the National SWM Fund in accordance with their guidelines;
assist the barangays in the establishment of their MRF;
continue to enhance awareness of constituents on SWM and develop stricter and more effective implementation techniques of SWM guidelines and ordinances; and
through the Sanggunian Bayan, expedite the passing of pending ordinances relative to SWM that will ensure the protection of public health and environment.

We have recommended that management:

submit the lacking documents to support the validity of the cash advance;

henceforth, refrain from using cash advance for purposes other than what it was granted for.

- Exert diligent effort to locate documents pertaining to said receivables and send demand letters to concerned individuals/suppliers and or deduct from future claims of employees or suppliers whatever is due from them.

- Direct the Municipal Accountant to conduct a thorough review on the circumstances surrounding the credit balances of receivables and make the necessary adjustments;

 Consider filing a request for authority to write-off vague receivables from the Central Office of the Commission on Audit pursuant to Section 4, Rule IV of the 2009 Revised Rules of Procedures.
